@startuml 33_interactive_flows_sequence
!theme plain
title DRE 3D Framework -- Interactive Flows (Rule Authoring + Diagnosis Query)

skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #546E7A
  LifeLineBorderColor #B0BEC5
  ParticipantBorderColor #90A4AE
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #ECEFF1
  BoxBorderColor #CFD8DC
}

box "User Layer" #FFF3E0
  actor "User" as User
end box

box "Databricks Apps (Frontend)" #E3F2FD
  participant "Chatbot UI\n(Streamlit)" as UI
end box

box "LangGraph Orchestration" #E8F5E9
  participant "LangGraph\nOrchestrator" as LG
  participant "Intent Router\nAgent" as IntentAgent
  participant "Retrieval\nAgent" as RetrievalAgent
  participant "SQL Generator\nAgent" as SQLAgent
  participant "Log Analysis\nAgent" as LogAgent
end box

box "AI & RAG" #FFF8E1
  participant "Model Serving\nLLM Endpoint" as LLM
  participant "Databricks\nAI Search" as VS
end box

box "Validation Pipeline" #FFCDD2
  participant "Security\nGuard" as SecGuard
  participant "Governance\nLayer" as GovLayer
  participant "SQL\nOptimizer" as SQLOpt
  participant "Duplicate\nDetector" as DupDetect
  participant "SQL\nValidator" as SQLVal
end box

box "Unity Catalog Delta" #E3F2FD
  database "anomaly_check_config" as RuleDB
  database "incident_context +\nevidence_log" as IncidentDB
  database "agent_session_log" as SessionLog
end box

box "External Systems" #FFF9C4
  participant "Jira" as Jira
end box

==INTERACTIVE FLOW 1: Rule Authoring==

User -> UI : "Create null check for customer.email"
activate UI

UI -> LG : {user_query, session_id}
activate LG

LG -> SessionLog : Log session start
LG -> IntentAgent : classify_intent(query)
activate IntentAgent

IntentAgent -> LLM : "Classify: READ or WRITE intent?"
LLM --> IntentAgent : "WRITE: Rule creation"

IntentAgent -> LLM : "Extract entities:\ntable, column, check_type"
LLM --> IntentAgent : {table: "customer",\ncolumn: "email",\ncheck_type: "null_rate"}

IntentAgent --> LG : Intent: RULE_CREATE\nEntities: {table, column, check_type}
deactivate IntentAgent

LG -> RetrievalAgent : retrieve_context(entities, check_type)
activate RetrievalAgent

RetrievalAgent -> VS : CAG: Load static context
VS --> RetrievalAgent : {supported_checks.md,\nsecurity_patterns.json,\npii_catalog.json}

RetrievalAgent -> VS : CRAG: embed_and_search(\n"null_rate customer email",\ntop_k=8,\nfilter={doc_type: "sql_pattern"})
VS --> RetrievalAgent : Top-8 chunks\n(confidence: 0.87 HIGH)

RetrievalAgent --> LG : Context assembled\n(CAG + CRAG)
deactivate RetrievalAgent

LG -> SQLAgent : generate_sql(context, entities)
activate SQLAgent

SQLAgent -> LLM : Generate SQL\n(grounded by CAG+CRAG)
LLM --> SQLAgent : SQL + explanation

SQLAgent --> LG : Generated SQL
deactivate SQLAgent

LG -> SecGuard : validate_security(sql)
activate SecGuard
SecGuard -> SecGuard : Check SELECT-only,\nforbidden keywords
SecGuard --> LG : PASSED
deactivate SecGuard

LG -> GovLayer : check_governance(table, column)
activate GovLayer
GovLayer -> RuleDB : Query PII catalog
RuleDB --> GovLayer : table.email = PII
GovLayer --> LG : PII flag\n(requires DataGov approval)
deactivate GovLayer

LG -> SQLOpt : optimize_sql(sql, table)
activate SQLOpt
SQLOpt -> RuleDB : Query UC metadata
RuleDB --> SQLOpt : Schema + partition info
SQLOpt -> LLM : Optimize query plan
LLM --> SQLOpt : Optimized SQL + cost estimate
SQLOpt --> LG : Optimized (cost: 2.3 DBU)
deactivate SQLOpt

LG -> DupDetect : check_duplicate(sql, table, column)
activate DupDetect
DupDetect -> VS : Vector search (similar rules)
VS --> DupDetect : Top-5 candidates
DupDetect -> LLM : Semantic comparison
LLM --> DupDetect : No duplicate (similarity < 85%)
DupDetect --> LG : NO_DUPLICATE
deactivate DupDetect

LG -> SQLVal : validate_sql(optimized_sql)
activate SQLVal
SQLVal -> RuleDB : DESCRIBE table
RuleDB --> SQLVal : Schema confirmed
SQLVal -> LLM : Logical validation
LLM --> SQLVal : Valid (quality: 9.2/10)
SQLVal --> LG : VALID
deactivate SQLVal

LG -> RuleDB : INSERT rule\n(status: PENDING_APPROVAL,\nis_active: false)
RuleDB --> LG : rule_id: DQ_20260702_001

LG -> Jira : Create approval ticket\n(requires DataGov approval)
Jira --> LG : ticket_id: TDA-5678

LG -> SessionLog : Log session complete\n(success)

LG --> UI : {rule_id, status: "Pending Approval",\napproval_sla: "48h", ticket_id}
deactivate LG

UI --> User : "✓ Rule DQ_20260702_001 created\nApproval request: TDA-5678\nSLA: 48 hours"
deactivate UI

note right
  <b>Interactive Flow 1 Complete</b>
  
  User creates rule via chatbot
  LangGraph orchestrates agents
  Multi-layer validation
  Approval routed via policy
  
  A2A Communication:
  - Agents share state via LangGraph
  - No direct agent-to-agent calls
end note

==INTERACTIVE FLOW 2: Diagnosis Query==

User -> UI : "Why did customer pipeline fail yesterday?"
activate UI

UI -> LG : {user_query, session_id}
activate LG

LG -> SessionLog : Log session start
LG -> IntentAgent : classify_intent(query)
activate IntentAgent

IntentAgent -> LLM : "Classify: READ or WRITE?"
LLM --> IntentAgent : "READ: Diagnosis query"

IntentAgent -> LLM : "Extract entities:\npipeline_id, date_range"
LLM --> IntentAgent : {pipeline: "customer",\ndate: "yesterday"}

IntentAgent --> LG : Intent: DIAGNOSIS_QUERY\nEntities: {pipeline, date}
deactivate IntentAgent

LG -> LogAgent : analyze_incident(pipeline, date)
activate LogAgent

LogAgent -> IncidentDB : Query incident_context\nWHERE pipeline_id LIKE '%customer%'\nAND detected_at >= yesterday

IncidentDB --> LogAgent : Matching incidents (2)

LogAgent -> IncidentDB : Load evidence_bundle\nFOR incident_id

IncidentDB --> LogAgent : {job_log_ref, delta_history,\nroot_cause, resolution}

LogAgent -> VS : RAG: Search incident_kb\n(similar incidents)
VS --> LogAgent : Historical patterns (3)

LogAgent -> LLM : Summarize diagnosis\n(evidence + context + history)

LLM --> LogAgent : "Pipeline failed at 14:00 UTC due to\nschema mismatch. Column 'email' was\nrenamed to 'email_address'.\nRoot cause: Deployment at 13:45.\nResolution: Schema migration applied.\nStatus: Resolved at 14:23 UTC."

LogAgent --> LG : Structured diagnosis response
deactivate LogAgent

LG -> SessionLog : Log session complete\n(diagnosis retrieved)

LG --> UI : {diagnosis_summary, evidence_refs,\ntimeline, resolution_status}
deactivate LG

UI --> User : "Pipeline failed due to schema mismatch...\n\n📋 Root Cause: Column renamed\n⏰ Failed: 14:00 UTC\n✓ Resolved: 14:23 UTC\n\n[View Evidence] [View Timeline]"
deactivate UI

note right
  <b>Interactive Flow 2 Complete</b>
  
  User queries past incidents
  LangGraph routes to LogAgent
  Agent retrieves evidence from Delta
  RAG searches incident_kb
  LLM summarizes for user
  
  A2A Communication:
  - LangGraph orchestrates
  - Agent reads Delta directly
  - RAG provides context
end note

legend right
  <b>Interactive Flows Summary</b>
  
  <b>Flow 1: Rule Authoring (WRITE)</b>
    User → UI → LangGraph → Agents
    → (Intent Router → Retrieval → SQL Generator)
    → LLM + AI Search (CAG + CRAG)
    → Validation Pipeline (5 stages)
    → Delta (PENDING_APPROVAL)
    → Jira (Approval Request)
  
  <b>Flow 2: Diagnosis Query (READ)</b>
    User → UI → LangGraph → Agents
    → (Intent Router → Log Analysis)
    → Delta (incident_context + evidence_log)
    → AI Search (incident_kb)
    → LLM (Summarize)
    → UI (Human-readable response)
  
  <b>Key Characteristics:</b>
  - <b>Synchronous:</b> User waits for response
  - <b>Stateful:</b> LangGraph maintains session state
  - <b>Multi-agent:</b> Specialized agents per task
  - <b>A2A via State:</b> Agents don't call each other
  - <b>LLM-intensive:</b> Reasoning at every step
  - <b>RAG-grounded:</b> CAG + CRAG ensure accuracy
  
  <b>Technologies:</b>
  - Databricks Apps (UI)
  - LangGraph (Orchestration)
  - Model Serving Endpoint (LLM)
  - AI Search (RAG)
  - Unity Catalog (Data)
  - External APIs (Jira)
endlegend

@enduml
